      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="37501425">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/WoSeMa/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1508735-1.jpg" alt="魔笛" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/37501425/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/37501425/" class="">第12页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/WoSeMa/" class=" " title="魔笛">魔笛</a>
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="37501425">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">翻译很差，注意不要被中文翻译误导。比如译文为

，也许这不是中国缺少借贷方面的实践，而是因为中国缺少金融或有权等法律实践。事实上，正如第三章所表明的那样，当时中国就有一个以当铺为基础的证券化借贷的案例。

英文原文是
This is not because China lacked a history of lending or of legal certification of financial claims. Indeed, as chapter 3 indicates, China not only possessed a sophisticated mercanti...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-04-02 20:29</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                翻译很差，注意不要被中文翻译误导。比如译文为<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>，也许这不是中国缺少借贷方面的实践，而是因为中国缺少金融或有权等法律实践。事实上，正如第三章所表明的那样，当时中国就有一个以当铺为基础的证券化借贷的案例。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>英文原文是
<blockquote><q>This is not because China lacked a history of lending or of legal certification of financial claims. Indeed, as chapter 3 indicates, China not only possessed a sophisticated mercantile court system but also an early securitized retail lending tradition based upon pawnshops.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>任何一个稍微认真学习过英文的同学都不会认为翻译是准确的；非但如此，译文太误导人，影响了大家的基本辨识能力及其从而生成的趣味，流毒深远，不可不防。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>其他的地方，随意插入译文的，比如<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>原文为
<blockquote><q>, and Europe learned first how to exploit the dimension of time.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>中文的译文居然成了
<blockquote><q>欧洲人首先学会了如何利用时间维度，首先学会了如何理解价值的跨时期转移。</q></blockquote>
Europe可以翻译成“欧洲人”也不管了，这后一句是哪里出来的？！这翻译，也是醉了
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

<a href="https://www.douban.com/accounts/register?reason=collect" class="j a_show_login lnk-sharing lnk-douban-sharing">推荐</a>
